    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i don't think there are any \"small moments\" left. i've tried finding them. it just feels like i'm dragging this heavy, useless shell of a person through the days. if the core of who i am—the part that actually felt alive—is gone, then what am i actually protecting? it feels like i'm just holding onto a ghost.",
